::Striker/Ramulus/Firearm/Rex/Smokescreen/Kluster::

"YEAH!" Firearm yells as the two attackers get blown out of the field. The 
big Maximal was still eager for battle, but victory was a welcome thing also. 
He looks around, then walking off toward the CR chambers.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Ramulus smiles as the attackers are neutralized. He too turns, heading for 
the CR chambers, followed by Striker and Smokescreen.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Rex grins. They had won agian! This mission wasn't as difficult as the elders 
had assured them....

He looks around the battlefield. "Anyone need help to a CR chamber?" he asks.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Kluster glances at the scanners and exterior visuals. The fighting seemed to 
have stopped, and there were no enemies detected aproaching the Cybertronian 
Fire.

"Maximals," he says into his comm, set on all Maximal frequences, "The battle 
at the Cybertronian Fire is over. We won."

With that, he looks back at Phobia's messenger, waiting for some action from 
it. He frowns as the scanners beep, looking at them to see a ship leaving the 
planet.

"Computer, scan ship."

"Negative. Ship out of scanning range."

"Anything?"

"The ship is of Predacon/Decepticon origin."

Kluster frowns again. "Scan predacon base."

He looks at the results, noting a decrease of bots. His frown deepens. So the 
Predacons have decided to leave?
